## Task tracking

This repo uses `todo-sqlite-cli` for TODOs. The DB path is resolved via the
`.todo-sqlite-cli` marker at the repo root (or `$TODO_SQLITE_CLI_DB`, or the
`--db` flag — in that precedence order).

**Before planning or coding, ask the DB — do not read a PLAN.md file:**

- `todo-sqlite-cli next` — the single task to work on right now. Returns
  the oldest in-progress task, or the highest-priority unblocked pending
  task, in one query. Prefer this over loading a plan file into context.
- `todo-sqlite-cli list` — all active (in-progress + pending) tasks, ordered
  in-progress first, then by priority.
- `todo-sqlite-cli show <id>` — full details for one task.
- `todo-sqlite-cli list --json` / `show <id> --json` / `next --json` — same
  output in machine-readable form.

**When picking up work:**

- `todo-sqlite-cli start <id>` before coding. At most one task may be
  in-progress at a time; use `--force` only when you deliberately want to
  suspend the current task.
- `todo-sqlite-cli done <id>` when the change is committed. Idempotent —
  safe to call twice.

**When a new task surfaces:**

- `todo-sqlite-cli add "title" --details "..." --tag <area> --priority <1-5>`
  (priority 1 is highest, 3 is default).
- `--depends-on <id>` to link a prerequisite. Tasks with unmet dependencies
  are skipped by `next` and flagged `[blocked]` in `list`.

**Exit codes:** 0 success, 1 user error, 2 system error. Every command
supports `--json` and `--db PATH`.
